          "TITLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Molybdenum-99 fission yield in the thermal neutron-",
                "induced fission of plutonium-239 and uranium-235."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "REAC"
                ],
                "institute": "3INDTRM"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " CIRUS-reactor"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SPECT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The Cd-ratio for contribution to fission products or",
                "cobalt activation was greater than 200"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Accurately weighed solutions of purified plutonium (an-",
                "alyzed for Pu-239 content) and nat. uranium respective-",
                "ly were evaporated on superpure Al-foil and wrapped",
                "in another Al-foil. The targets contained about",
                "10 micro-g of Pu-239 or U-235."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "CHSEP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " After irradiation, the targets were dissolved.",
                "A known amount of Mo-carrier was added to an aliquot",
                "of the solution. Mo was then separated, purified and",
                "precipitated as lead-molybdate. After determining the",
                "chemical yield, macro-samples of about 20 mg precipit-",
                "ate weight on standard Al-plates with double-coated",
                "cellulose tape, covered with 3 mg/cm2 thick cellophane",
                "paper, were mounted for beta-counting."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "PROPC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ". End-window methane gas flow, 4pi-geometry."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GELI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ". For purity check and beta-gamma coincidence."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DECAY-DATA": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "flag": null,
                "nuclide": "42-MO-99",
                "half-life": {
                  "value": 66.18,
                  "unit": "HR"
                },
                "radiation": []
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Determined by following the decay of",
                "more than 60 samples."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Compiler's comment: From a Cd-ratio=200 for Co-59, the",
                "epithermal index r=0.0022 is derived. In his 1977-",
                "evaluation, NEDO-12154-2, B.F. Rider assumed a neutron",
                "temperature of T=40 deg.C. The values r and t were used",
                "for a re-evaluation by M.Lammer (Sympos. on Nucl. Data",
                "in Science and Technology, Paris,1973,vol.1,P.505)."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "STATUS": [
